---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import LegalDoc from '../components/LegalDoc.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | EMLinter"
  description="The simple terms for using EMLinter's free HTML email tools — fair use, your content, our content, and no-warranty basics. No signup required."
>
  <LegalDoc heading="Terms of Service" updated="July 13, 2026">
    <p>Welcome to EMLinter. By using our website and free HTML email tools (the "Service"), you agree to these simple terms. If you have any questions, just <a href="/contact-us">get in touch</a>.</p>

    <h2>Using the Service</h2>
    <p>EMLinter is a free set of browser-based tools for building, validating, formatting, minifying, and testing HTML email. No account is required. Please use the Service fairly — don't use it for anything illegal or harmful (such as creating spam or phishing email), and don't try to disrupt or abuse the site or resell it as your own product.</p>

    <h2>Your Content</h2>
    <p>Anything you paste, upload, or create with the tools stays yours. The tools process your content locally in your browser, so in normal use it never reaches our servers. You're responsible for making sure you have the right to use the content you work with.</p>

    <h2>Our Content</h2>
    <p>The EMLinter software, design, name, and logo belong to us. You're welcome to use the templates and code snippets we share in your own email projects — just don't repackage or resell them as a standalone template product.</p>

    <h2>No Warranty</h2>
    <p>The Service is provided free, "as is." We work hard to keep it accurate and reliable, but we can't guarantee that every result renders perfectly in every email client, so please test your email before sending. To the extent allowed by law, we aren't liable for any loss arising from use of the Service.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may improve, change, or update the Service and these terms over time. When we update the terms, we'll revise the "Last updated" date above.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about these terms? Reach us via the <a href="/contact-us">Contact Us</a> page.</p>
  </LegalDoc>
</BaseLayout>
